    {
        "content": "<p>So it is <code>rustfmt</code> that is crashing, not <code>rustc</code></p>",
        "id": 423973794,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1709196571
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"607542\">@Ariel Miculas</span> if you still want to expand something, what you can do is find the <code>.cmd</code> file for your rust object. It has the command line used to invoke <code>rustc</code>. You can then add <code>-Zunpretty=expanded</code> and <code>RUSTC_BOOTSTRAP=1</code> to that command line and run it in a shell. That works.</p>",
        "id": 423980342,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1709199155
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>thanks, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"498029\">@Andreas Hindborg</span></p>",
        "id": 424012400,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1709211128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Using.20the.20.2Ersi.20target/near/423973794\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>So it is <code>rustfmt</code> that is crashing, not <code>rustc</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Minimized:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>: <span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">builtin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">offset_of</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>rustfmt</code> ICEs (apparently on purpose) on certain expanded <code>-Zunpretty=expanded</code> constructs (e.g. <code>offset_of!</code>).</p>\n<p>Reported it here: <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rustfmt/issues/6105\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rustfmt/issues/6105</a>.</p>",
        "id": 424723435,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1709578448
    }
